	   <tr><td colspan=2>bonus Hp is bonus Hp, especialy for low level characters. AT first level this would be GODLY, by 5th level it's a nice little bonus. Decent speed, great damage potential later, a little AC (which, if you have bothered to twink a character won't matter at all because it should be at the AC cap until it reaches at least 15th level or longer) and the all important to twinks bonus HP (swinging speed and bonus HP are about the only things that arn't nerfed for low level characters. If your making a serious twink, go for low delay, bonus HP, and any kind of regen you can get. AC is nice, but it gets capped. Same for damage and mana. Stats are a distand third, but something to keep in mind. Might as well ignore saves till you reach 40's. Sure saves are great, but other things are more important for quite a while.)<br>&nbsp;<br>Meirril, Fennin Ro</td></tr>
